Technique Distance Swim
## Warm-up
• 400m easy freestyle at base pace + 10-15 seconds per 100m
• 200m choice stroke (backstroke or breaststroke) focusing on form

## Main Set

### Distance Block 1
• 800m freestyle at base pace + 5 seconds per 100m
• Focus on **long, smooth strokes** and bilateral breathing
• Maintain consistent stroke count per length

### Technique Focus
4 x 200m freestyle:
• 50m catch-up drill (one arm at a time)
• 50m fingertip drag drill
• 100m normal freestyle at base pace
• **Rest 30 seconds between each 200m**

### Distance Block 2
• 600m freestyle at base pace + 3 seconds per 100m
• Focus on **high elbow catch** and strong finish
• Count strokes every 4th length to maintain efficiency

## Cool-down
• 200m easy choice stroke
• Focus on **relaxed breathing** and smooth rhythm

EMBED_STR:
Advanced Hill Sprints
## Warm-up
• 1500m easy run to prepare muscles and joints
• Include dynamic stretches focusing on calves and hamstrings

## Main Set
### Hill Sprint Intervals
8 rounds of:
• 90 seconds uphill sprint at **maximum effort** (8-10% grade preferred)
• Focus on driving knees high and maintaining quick turnover
• 3 minutes active recovery walking/jogging back down

**Key Tips:**
• Find a consistent hill with steady grade
• Sprint at 95-100% effort - this should feel unsustainable
• Use the downhill recovery to prepare mentally for next interval
• Maintain good form even when fatigued

## Cool-down
• 1500m easy jog on flat terrain
• Follow with thorough stretching routine
